Good morning,

This week=E2=80=99s interview is with one of the intellectual forbearers of=
 Stratechery: the Boston Sports Guy, Bill Simmons ( https://twitter.com/bil=
lsimmons ). I first encountered Simmons in my college dorm room when he joi=
ned ESPN=E2=80=99s Page 2; I devoured every column he wrote for years, and =
was an instant listener to the B.S. Report, the podcast he launched in 2007=
. While at ESPN Simmons launched Grantland, one of my favorite Internet pro=
perties of all time; after a messy divorce with ESPN, Simmons founded The R=
inger ( https://www.theringer.com/ ) website and podcast network, which was=
 acquired by Spotify in 2020. Today Simmons continues to host his eponymous=
 podcast, run The Ringer, and plays an increasingly important role in Spoti=
fy=E2=80=99s overall podcast strategy.

